<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Madison, WI Territorials 6/8/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.78)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2645'>Christian "ck1" Kriesel</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2645&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 13, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Pre-Tourney: <br>
<br>
I have plans to go to Madison and spend the night at my friend Dan&#39;s house on Friday night. Thursday night, I&#39;m making decks like mad. I put the finishing touches up on them and end up with 5 completed decks. <br>
<br>
I end up driving an hour to Madison to the store and meet with Chris Wiemer, fellow rider. I ask to play a few games and he says &#39;sure&#39;. He&#39;s playing the Super Fellowship Fire deck with Uruk-Hai&#39;s. We split the first two games even though I get some terrible draws. All my cards are in order and I have no mixure most of them. He wins both. I get two more decks out and mix for what seemed like 30 minutes. I hope it works. I play hobbit stealth which is just nastry for his big uruk-hai&#39;s. I&#39;ve got his hand locked, but for the life of me I can&#39;t get any of the 4 Deftness in my hand before site 6. So, Sam takes a dive at site 5.  That&#39;s pretty much game. Then I go to Gandalf elves/hate deck. This one is really close, and I end up beating him to the end. He just can not stop me. We rematch and this time I can&#39;t stop him. <br>
TRIAL DECKS:<br>
Hobbit denial/Nazgul Freaks (great deck I want to try META)<br>
SuperFellowship/Uruk&#39;s (striaght forward)<br>
Moria Archery/Drawves discard (ended up needing more thought<br>
Uruk&#39;s/Ranger Choke (it&#39;s 18-4), but I&#39;m tired of playing it<br>
Super Gandalf Elves/Sauron Hate (no great combo&#39;s)<br>
<br>
I leave knowing that I have decks to build for tomorrow because I didn&#39;t like any of those. I get to Dan&#39;s later than expected and start building right away. I end up going with two ideas. Nazgul Freaks, and Super Mirror/Uruk-Hai. In bed at 4 AM. I&#39;m up bright and early even before the alarm goes off at 8:30AM. SSS...and I&#39;m off to the tournament with all my cards. <br>
<br>
Saturday: Territorial Tournament::<br>
<br>
I get there and notice a couple people not present which I can understand (the day was beautiful), but with this much at stake why not show? Some more players come in, deck lists are verified and turned in. Chris says I shouldn&#39;t check decks because I&#39;m playing. I&#39;m like - np. I get other things set up and I turn in my SuperElves/Uruk&#39;s deck list. He checks the deck and at 11AM, we are ready to go. <br>
<br>
Merry (-2 G/A) and Boromir, LoG start throughout the day. Green Dragon Inn is my site 1. <br>
My rating going in is 1678. <br>
<br>
First game vs. Michael Laundy (Nazgul/Ranger stuff)<br>
<br>
This guy is from Mt Horeb and didn&#39;t know of the tournament until he can to the Star Trek Territorial at Misty. He bids 4 to my 3 and goes first. D@mn! I wanted to get out Sam and go first against this newbie. (mistake #1 already!) He gets out the pony starting Sam and Arwen. exerts and is down to two burdens. I put out an Uruk-Hai, but he is playing Ranger pump w/Swordsman, No Mere Ranger, ect. I lose, but he stop. I get out Aragorn, Flaming Brand, sword and move 1-3 with little resistance. He gets out Gandalf, armor moves 2-4 with those dumb pump cards. He takes a long time on decisions and I can&#39;t wound his characters. I give Boromir FB, LastAoEaM. Move (did you see the mistake? boromir is now S13 vs. Nazgul. Aragorn is S13 vs. Nazgul. I should have put both FB on Boromir). I don&#39;t reply the brand the rest of the game. Of course, WK S14comes down, and I can&#39;t beat him. Boromir and Aragorn take care of the other and I move twice stopping at 5. He moves to 5 and has to stop. I go 6 and think I have this game won. He goes to 6 and stops to heal. I go and don&#39;t 6-8 meeting the WK again. Still, not much damage. He slowly goes to 7..then pauses and moves to 8. I&#39;m like who cares. It&#39;s over. TIME! is called. Shot it&#39;s going to be a timed win. Oh well. I ask if he would like to sacrifice Frodo vs. Lurtz on the Fierce skirmish. He declines and kills off Aragorn. The last companion and I think I&#39;ve won. But wait it goes to burdens doesn&#39;t it? Well, no Sam the entire game and I&#39;ve lost 3 Burdens to 1. Great. I had an easy, EASY win and blow it. Nice way to start the day. <br>
<br>
Mistakes: Flaming Brand on Boromir could have sped the game.<br>
Bidding low. Not getting Sam. Might have crippled him with only Arwen and Sam. One could have died first turn and the armor&#39;s could have been stuck in his hand. WI<br>
Timed Lose (1) <br>
<br>
Game 2 vs. Jeremy Janik (Nazgul/Gandalf Fire)<br>
<br>
I&#39;ve seen decks like this on decktech - thanks everyone. So, I&#39;ve got a small advantage. He isn&#39;t play massive party though. Only 4-6 guys. I&#39;m running 9 if they all get in play. I bid 5. He bids 6. Lose Sam again, wtf!? He plays the Pony. I get Sam opening hand. Where were you last game Mr. Gamgee?  Well, I get some magic with the FB again. This time no mistakes. He knows pretty quick he&#39;s going to lose. He can&#39;t find any of the 3/3 Blade/BBreath. I&#39;m moving fast and he can&#39;t keep up. No huge skirmish&#39;s. But I pull Enquea first turn and kill off his armored Boromir. I win at site 9. Even after he drew 5 more cards. Nazgul just don&#39;t usually need the spare draws. The end was ugly though. He pounded the table, put his head down, and didn&#39;t move for a few minutes. All the while I&#39;m picking up my cards wondering if he&#39;s going to go balistic soon. I know the feeling driving a long ways and knowing you are pretty much out of the tournament after 2 games. IL<br>
NO Mistakes! yea, haw<br>
Full Win (4)<br>
<br>
LUNCH! <br>
Me and my friend Mark decide to split and go to KFC for some good food. We both didn&#39;t want Rocky&#39;s or McD&#39;s. We wanted something fast, but not too greasy. I get the #2 and Mark order&#39;s the Chicken Wrap. We talk about decks and the fact I lost one of the slowest players I&#39;ve ever played. Time flies by and we grab a soda for the road and we are out of there. <br>
 <br>
Game 3 vs Adam Molnar <br>
<br>
He came all the way up from Chicago, and I&#39;m ready to finally win a opening bid. He plays like his friend and I figure a high bid. So, I go 7. I win get same and move to 2. Again, Nazgul. I stop. He sets up and moves to 2 stopping for his sight 3. I go and survive, but I&#39;m hurting. That&#39;s cool though people need to die anyways. He moves to 3 and stops. I go to 5 with some Brands popping up and a nice fellowship to take everything not to mention my Thror&#39;s Map - only game I saw it. The race is on. He has to stop at 4, and I go to 6. Drawing 2 ARV&#39;s. I&#39;m set. He has to stop at 6 and I get some more help cards. I get everything out. He drops WK w/PB, Cantea. I play ARV, and archery kills him. Move again...pretty much same thing happens. ARV everything dies. He know&#39;s he can&#39;t win. He moves to 8. I go to 9 and win easily. <br>
Again, no Mistakes. <br>
Full Win (7)<br>
<br>
So, now I&#39;ll have to face the top competition to get into the finals. <br>
<br>
Game 4 vs Michael Frye Stealth/Basic Party-Sauron Swarm<br>
<br>
Michael plays decks that look like starter decks, and he <br>
wins often. I played him in Star Wars way back. He always had great ideas, and is very creative, intellegent, etc. <br>
I bid 5 and win. We both had Green Dragon Inn though. I get an unbelieve GOD draw for the Mirro, but no Mirror. Galadriel, Elrond, Celeborn, and Orophrin all hit the table. Then I exert Elrond and find Arwen, but Galadriel is exhausted. So, I don&#39;t play her and hope to make it to 3. Sam (3W), Merry, Frodo w/Ring, Boromir. I move and he has 3 minions 2 Moria Scouts, and 6 power Sauron Tracker. This is great. Do, I put Frodo up against one of the 6&#39;s, and keep Merry or Sam alive? Well, I don&#39;t chance it and decide to stop. Because if he gets down 2 more guys that&#39;s game. He moves slowly too. I get to 3, and I&#39;m set with the mirror. Of course, he&#39;s playing the Sauron Exert wound Ally. Elrond gets it first, and later Galadriel herself bites the dirt.  Back and forth on moving. Here&#39;s some cool stuff. He plays Throw Yourself In Next Time on my site 2 move. No big deal right? Well, site 4 Marsh, and I can&#39;t exert Frodo. How&#39;s that for tech? He KNOWS I&#39;m playing Wariness too. I have 3 in the deck just for this game. He plays Stealth at site 4 and 5. Of course, I don&#39;t have a single Wariness in my hand. I can&#39;t get anything good out to kill him off and he&#39;s got armor out too. On site 5, it&#39;s going to be close because of the shadow I&#39;ve given him. It wasn&#39;t much, and I held back some minor stuff. He looks at me and I know I&#39;ve screwed him over. He says just one more shadow and Frodo is overwhelmed or facing 3 guys. He can&#39;t do it and suffices with not much. I usually beat everyone of his guys. The deck is a swarm deck. My fellowship is huge now at 5. So, I go 5-7 and he can NOT stop me. I figure he&#39;s just lost because he&#39;s sitting at 6. He moves to 7 and stops. I go to 8 and it&#39;s the slopes. I&#39;m thinking no way is he going to get 5 out with my 5 companions now. He play the Nazgul 4+=pull 1 minion from lost pile (orc). 3 Orcs from hand. Discards 3 cards from hand to play the 5th orc from discard pile with TheyAC. Great, he&#39;s got me now. I win everything and am forced to stop. He knows he can&#39;t stop me. So, he goes 7-9 and I can not kill off Frodo. <br>
Mistakes..Site 2. Should have moved again. Still no Map.wtf?<br>
That would have been risky, but won me the game. I should have thought to kill one more guy off, but I think he would have had an easier chance that way too. <br>
<br>
Good game..both sides. <br>
I&#39;ve heard about the deck, but I never KNEW what it consisted of. Now I do..<br>
Full Loss. (8)<br>
Now, I know I have to win every game just to have a chance. <br>
<br>
Game 5 vs. Todd Richardson Uruk&#39;s/Gandalf Servant<br>
<br>
This game was the worst draws for me the entire day. He had everything on his turn and I couldn&#39;t do anything. I think I could have triple moved first turn because he dropped every card but 1 on his first turn. I stop at 2. He just moves. There isn&#39;t much to say. I do get the mirror set up pretty fast. He&#39;s mad, but I can&#39;t get anything useful. So, it sucks and there&#39;s not much I can do. Double moves the entire game except site 2. Yep even at 4 where he didn&#39;t buy my bluff. Didn&#39;t see a single savagery until site 8 when I drew 3. <br>
No Mistakes just horrible draws. <br>
Full Loss (9)<br>
I&#39;m pretty much out of it. So, I&#39;m on cruise control now. <br>
<br>
Game 6 vs Carl Hooker Arwen-Sam/Moria Swarm,CT,&#39;Rog<br>
<br>
This guy is from San Diego, CA? Wow! Nice to see you Carl. I go first and I&#39;m set up. He gets the worst hand a person can get. I stop at 2 with 15 shadow in the pool. He drops almost his entire hand and moves to 2. Stopping at 2 also. I go to his 3 and it&#39;s the ranger +1 site. So, I stop at 3. He goes to 4 and is forced to stop with my minions bearing down on him. I go to 4-nothing..hmm..move to 5 (20shawdow)-nothing..that means no &#39;Rog. So, I go to 6 thanks to his site 3! ;-) He gets out a Troll finally that finished off Merry. Too bad, hobbit of some intellegent! He gets to 6, but isn&#39;t set up shawdow yet. It&#39;s pretty much over. I don&#39;t make the site 8 mistake again. I move right to 8. Oh, I&#39;ve also got an ARV. So, the first troll that comes down gets it square in the nuts...via Legolas. He moves, but no helpers on the moving side. Stopping at 7. I go to 9, and archery my way out of a couple and that&#39;s game. <br>
<br>
No mistakes: too bad about his bad draws. 4 minions through site 6. not including the troll and Balrog in his hand.<br>
Full WIn (12)<br>
<br>
So, the day winds up. I predict I&#39;ll end up in 5th place. They call the final rounds and my friend Mark finishes last with his Nazgul deck. On up to 5th place..ME! I thought so. Close, but no cigar. I get 4 packs and pull a Boromir, Morgul Gates. No bad. <br>
<br>
The Finals are Michael Frye vs. (not sure) Chuck Evers<br>
<br>
I&#39;m not sure about the final. He didn&#39;t win though. Michael did. I&#39;ll find out for you if you want me to. I didn&#39;t watch the game because it was untimed and they decided to play a clean game over 45 minutes rather than rush and get it over with. So, I ended up trading. I got some c/u foils. If anyone has lots that they are looking to get rid of email me. I get a Blade of Gondor FOIL, Attea FOIL, and some other good stuff. I made a huge SW:TCG trade for LotR foils and cards. <br>
<br>
<br>
End Game: <br>
<br>
I drop Dan off at home, and decide to drive home after 4 hours of sleep. I stop for a bite to eat. I drop my change in the drive through and reach to pick it up. I thought the car ahead of me had gone. So, as I&#39;m reaching down I step off the brake and hit the car ahead of me. Thank GOD! I wasn&#39;t going fast and there was no damage. I get my cheeseburger&#39;s and I&#39;m out of there lickity-split. I call Dan to stay awake and make it home safe from there. Onto, IL Territorials next! <br>
<br>
